# 1) REQUIRED SOFTWARE

* bwa v0.7.12-r1039
* bowtie2 v2.2.6
* fastqc v0.11.4
* scan_for_matches
* samtools v1.3.1

On Ubuntu, run: `sudo apt install bwa bowtie2 fastqc`

Download scan_for_matches from http://www.theseed.org/servers/downloads/scan_for_matches.tgz
Follow the instruction to install it: http://blog.theseed.org/servers/2010/07/scan-for-matches.html
Then, add the path of the uncompressed (with uncompress) folder to your $PATH env variable with: `export PATH=$PATH:path_to_scan_for_matches`

If, after installation, fastqc complains of missing files, download them from:
https://github.com/ggirelli/configs/tree/master/fastqc/Configuration

# 2) REQUIRED R LIBRARIES

* argparser
* data.table
* ggplot2
* grid
* gridExtra
* parallel
* readr
* reshape2

Install them from within R with the `install.packages()` command.
Or run the INSTALL.R script.

# 3) REQUIRED PYTHON LIBRARIES

* argparse
* sys

Install them with `pip install`.

# 4) FOLDERS

Need a ~/tmp folder for sorting.
